Citation.sAbstract: Experimental densities were obtained in the binary mixtures water + 3-ethoxypropan-1-amine, for the whole composition range and at temperatures between (283.15 and 303.15) K. Derived thermodynamic properties such as apparent molar, excess molar, and excess partial molar volumes have been calculated. Limiting partial molar volumes and isobaric expansions were obtained for the two components. Different patterns of molecular aggregation and hydration schemes were detected.
Citation.sTitle: Volumetric Study of (3-Ethoxypropan-1-amine + Water) Mixtures between (283.15 and 303.15) K
